verbose_text: The 5-HT 1 receptor agonist sumatriptan (300 nM) decreased GABA B IPSCs (71.42% +/- 4.50% of control, n = 8) and largely occluded the inhibition produced by cocaine (cocaine alone = 67.53% +/- 3.01% of control, n = 19; sumatriptan + cocaine = 91.51% +/- 3.52% of control, n = 8; p < 0.001, one-way ANOVA, Bonferroni post hoc analysis; XREF_FIG).
